WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.720
ARTHUR: <i>In New York City, at 6am,</i>

00:02.840 --> 00:06.200
<i>the Wall Street Stock Exchange crashed.</i>

00:06.320 --> 00:09.240
THOMAS: <i>I told Michael on Friday
this was going to happen.</i>

00:09.360 --> 00:11.480
We were most definitely on board.

00:14.040 --> 00:16.360
But you have to listen
to the voices that you hear.

00:16.480 --> 00:18.200
<i>- (GUNSHOT)
. (HORSE NEIGHS)</i>

00:22.280 --> 00:24.720
My name is Mosley. Oswald Mosley.

00:24.840 --> 00:26.360
THOMAS: Yeah, I know who you are.

00:26.480 --> 00:28.360
You have come to my attention.

00:30.080 --> 00:32.920
Mr Shelby?
Mr Levitt from the <i>London Times.</i>

00:33.040 --> 00:35.920
Ten years ago, I was a journalist
on the <i>Birmingham Evening Mail.</i>

00:36.040 --> 00:37.840
Course, working in that city,

00:37.960 --> 00:39.960
it was impossible not to know your name.

00:40.080 --> 00:42.720
And your...reputation.

00:42.840 --> 00:45.880
What is your Tory newspaper
more afraid of?

00:46.000 --> 00:49.160
Is it evolution or revolution?

01:13.560 --> 01:15.400
(SIGHS)

01:18.800 --> 01:20.280
(GLASS RATTLES)

01:20.400 --> 01:22.280
(POURS LIQUID)

01:56.200 --> 01:59.040
(PHONE RINGS)

02:23.560 --> 02:26.000
(CROW CAWS)

02:52.440 --> 02:54.560
(CROW CAWS)

03:05.520 --> 03:08.360
(WIND HOWLS)

03:25.720 --> 03:28.760
(TICKING)

03:28.880 --> 03:32.480
(MUD SLOSHES)

04:11.840 --> 04:13.800
(SIGHS)

05:18.080 --> 05:19.640
(GROANS)

05:19.760 --> 05:23.360
DISTORTED CHILD'S VOICE:
Dad! There's a phone call for you!

05:28.760 --> 05:31.680
Dad! There's a phone call for you!

05:33.160 --> 05:34.200
THOMAS: Charlie!

05:35.720 --> 05:39.040
Charlie! Wait!

05:39.160 --> 05:40.360
Charlie!

05:56.280 --> 05:58.400
Giddy-up, horsey, giddy-up!

06:04.280 --> 06:08.200
- Dad, there's a phone call for you.
- Good boy.

06:08.320 --> 06:10.080
Good boy.

06:10.200 --> 06:12.160
Will you go back to the house?

06:12.280 --> 06:14.360
And, er, whoever's calling,

06:14.480 --> 06:17.000
the operator will have their number,

06:17.120 --> 06:19.080
and I'll call them back, eh?

06:19.200 --> 06:21.040
(CAR APPROACHES)

06:22.520 --> 06:23.720
Oh, look, Charlie.

06:23.840 --> 06:25.520
You must have violin practice.

06:25.640 --> 06:27.040
It's Mrs Milligan.

06:27.160 --> 06:28.160
Go on.

06:29.480 --> 06:30.640
And, Charlie!

06:30.760 --> 06:33.160
Charlie, you play loudly.

06:33.280 --> 06:35.000
You might hear some bangs.

06:36.120 --> 06:37.400
Go on.

06:50.960 --> 06:52.480
(SIGHS)

07:03.800 --> 07:06.120
(VIOLIN PRACTICE IN DISTANCE)

08:29.880 --> 08:31.400
OPERATOR: <i>Mr Shelby?</i>

08:31.520 --> 08:33.600
Maggie, yeah, it's me.

08:33.720 --> 08:35.920
<i>. Yes, Mr Shelby.</i>
- I just missed a call.

08:36.040 --> 08:37.320
Where was it from?

08:37.440 --> 08:39.040
<i>Belfast.</i>

08:39.160 --> 08:42.480
Belfast. Where in Belfast?

08:42.600 --> 08:44.600
<i>Um, I'm not sure.</i>

08:44.720 --> 08:46.440
Do you have the number?

08:46.560 --> 08:47.960
Yeah.

08:50.440 --> 08:51.960
Yeah, can you put me through?

08:52.080 --> 08:54.800
(STATIC)

08:57.120 --> 08:59.040
(STATIC STOPS)

09:00.120 --> 09:01.280
MICHAEL: <i>Tommy, don't believe...</i>

09:06.920 --> 09:08.920
Mr Shelby.

09:09.040 --> 09:10.520
My name is Captain Swing,

09:10.640 --> 09:12.480
calling from the occupied Six Counties.

09:12.600 --> 09:15.080
And there are some people
from the other side

09:15.200 --> 09:18.520
of our neat little city
that want you dead.

09:18.640 --> 09:24.480
<i>You should also know that this boy,
this Michael, your kin,</i>

09:24.600 --> 09:28.200
was in his cabin
aboard the SS Monroe in Belfast dock,

09:28.320 --> 09:30.920
making deals with the very men
who want you dead.

09:31.040 --> 09:31.960
Tommy, they're lying!

09:32.080 --> 09:35.560
Now, if you want, we can put
a bullet in his head here and now...

09:36.640 --> 09:38.680
...or we can send him home,
and you can deal with him.

09:45.000 --> 09:46.600
Send him home.

09:47.880 --> 09:49.560
Very well, Mr Shelby.

09:49.680 --> 09:53.880
But be informed that this kin of yours
was talking to representatives

09:54.000 --> 09:57.160
from the County Tyrone and Glasgow UVF

09:57.280 --> 09:59.200
about how they'd divide up
the English racetracks

09:59.320 --> 10:02.880
- after they'd blown away your legs.
- Tommy, they're lying!

10:05.400 --> 10:06.480
And may I ask...

10:07.680 --> 10:09.520
...why you are doing me this favour?

10:12.800 --> 10:13.960
Because, Mr Shelby,

10:14.080 --> 10:16.880
we've been informed
by people at the very highest level

10:17.000 --> 10:19.840
that, since your conversion to socialism,

10:19.960 --> 10:22.400
you are now on the side of the angels.

10:22.520 --> 10:25.640
And angels can be useful to us.

10:27.360 --> 10:28.800
(LINE DISCONNECTS)

10:46.400 --> 10:47.640
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

10:47.760 --> 10:49.160
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

10:51.680 --> 10:52.920
Come.

11:01.240 --> 11:04.840
Mr Shelby, the violin teacher
wants to know what all those bangs were.

11:05.960 --> 11:07.280
Fireworks.

11:07.400 --> 11:09.040
Was trying them out for Saturday.

11:12.320 --> 11:15.080
You promised the doctor
not until after dark.

11:16.360 --> 11:18.200
Oh, it's pretty dark, Frances.

11:21.480 --> 11:22.920
Also,

11:23.040 --> 11:26.320
will Mrs Shelby and Ruby be home
for dinner tonight?

11:26.440 --> 11:27.720
I don't know.

11:37.120 --> 11:38.160
CHARLES: Dad?

11:39.240 --> 11:41.440
I've learned something this morning.

11:41.560 --> 11:42.960
Have you?

11:45.840 --> 11:47.080
So have I.

11:48.400 --> 11:49.760
And what have you learned, my boy?

11:52.520 --> 11:55.520
(SCRATCHY TUNE ON VIOLIN)

12:12.680 --> 12:15.800
Let's get this over with.
I've got a train to catch.

12:15.920 --> 12:17.800
Go get your train, Tom.
I can deal with this.

12:17.920 --> 12:18.920
Oi.

12:19.040 --> 12:21.720
- (COINS CLINK)
- Get it!

12:41.040 --> 12:42.840
Go home.

12:45.440 --> 12:46.800
Come here, you.

12:46.920 --> 12:49.040
Put this on.

12:49.160 --> 12:51.680
There you go.
Look at that, it looks great on you.

12:51.800 --> 12:53.480
Wrap up warm.

13:04.880 --> 13:06.600
Ah!

13:06.720 --> 13:07.880
Wake up.

13:09.160 --> 13:11.160
Rise and shine.

13:11.280 --> 13:12.280
What are you doing here?

13:12.400 --> 13:14.400
Wasting our fucking time on you.

13:18.800 --> 13:20.400
Sit down, Finn.

13:20.520 --> 13:22.560
Sit down.

13:29.560 --> 13:30.800
What do I have to do...

13:32.080 --> 13:34.200
...to make you fucking listen to me?

13:34.320 --> 13:37.320
You took a bullet.

13:37.440 --> 13:39.840
You've been running around the streets
with a fucking gun in your hand.

13:42.080 --> 13:43.560
Somebody has to.

13:46.160 --> 13:48.560
Finn, we've got people
for that kind of work.

13:48.680 --> 13:52.320
Soldiers. Captains and corporals.

13:52.440 --> 13:53.720
Well, then, what am I?

13:55.200 --> 13:56.320
"What am I?" Jesus Christ.

13:56.440 --> 13:59.600
Yeah, what am I, Tom, huh?

13:59.720 --> 14:01.480
I'm the brother you never got round to.

14:02.520 --> 14:05.000
You're a general, Finn.

14:05.120 --> 14:06.280
You understand?

14:06.400 --> 14:09.600
You're a fucking Shelby,
so you're a general.

14:09.720 --> 14:13.720
When did you last see a general
anywhere near the blood and the puke, eh?

14:15.080 --> 14:17.280
He's fucking right.

14:17.400 --> 14:19.160
That's what you are.

14:19.280 --> 14:21.680
So on your feet, soldier.

14:21.800 --> 14:23.400
Come on, on your feet.

14:23.520 --> 14:26.120
I thought you just said I was a general.

14:26.240 --> 14:27.880
I did just say you were.

14:28.000 --> 14:29.360
So get on your fucking feet!

14:29.480 --> 14:31.160
Arthur...

14:31.280 --> 14:33.560
(SIGHS) Finn. Finn.

14:33.680 --> 14:34.800
Look at this.

14:34.920 --> 14:38.920
This is the bullet
that Aberama Gold cut from you.

14:39.040 --> 14:41.480
First and last.

14:42.880 --> 14:45.360
First and last.

14:50.400 --> 14:51.680
Don't lose it.

14:52.960 --> 14:55.680
Go and clean up, put some clothes on.

14:55.800 --> 14:57.440
A nice suit.

14:57.560 --> 14:59.960
I've got some trouble
that'll keep you out of trouble.

15:01.640 --> 15:04.080
- Oh, and, erm, Tom...
- Yeah?

15:04.200 --> 15:05.600
...while you're here,

15:05.720 --> 15:07.960
erm, I've met this girl

15:08.080 --> 15:10.200
- and I'd like to get married.
- Fuck off. Go, get dressed.

15:10.320 --> 15:11.320
Go on, move.

15:11.440 --> 15:12.680
Go!

15:12.800 --> 15:14.840
Finn, this girl you're trying to impress,

15:14.960 --> 15:16.360
tell me about her.

15:17.400 --> 15:18.800
She likes the life.

15:18.920 --> 15:21.040
She likes the life, eh?

15:21.160 --> 15:22.480
Well, find one that hates it.

15:22.600 --> 15:25.640
Look at him, that's what he did.
Now he's chairman of the board.

15:28.320 --> 15:29.680
Go on. Hurry up.

15:30.800 --> 15:31.840
Arthur?

15:31.960 --> 15:35.520
Lizzie and Ruby, are they still at yours?

15:38.480 --> 15:40.440
Yes, Tom, they're still there.

15:40.560 --> 15:43.080
She's coming home today, she said, so...

15:43.200 --> 15:44.600
...she'll be home later.

15:45.680 --> 15:48.360
Hm. Has she been talking about me?

15:48.480 --> 15:51.320
I mean, they talk a lot,
you know what women are like.

15:51.440 --> 15:54.320
The kitchen and, you know,
kids running around.

15:54.440 --> 15:56.440
I...I don't pay 'em no mind, Tom.

15:56.560 --> 15:58.440
- I don't listen to 'em 'alf the time.
- Yeah.

15:59.680 --> 16:01.120
Well, everything she says is true.

16:05.280 --> 16:06.560
Well...

16:08.920 --> 16:10.120
...you like the life, Tommy.

16:10.240 --> 16:12.200
I don't like the fucking life.

16:12.320 --> 16:14.040
I don't like the fucking life,

16:14.160 --> 16:16.440
I don't like
that Michael is coming back today.

16:19.920 --> 16:22.120
Train arrives from Liverpool at three.

16:22.240 --> 16:23.520
Polly will be there.

16:23.640 --> 16:24.760
Take a weapon.

16:25.880 --> 16:28.080
Tell Moss to clear the station of coppers.

16:28.200 --> 16:29.440
You hear me?

16:29.560 --> 16:30.600
Yes, sir.

16:32.960 --> 16:34.760
Hey, Tommy.

16:36.480 --> 16:38.440
I heard 'em say one thing, though.

16:39.720 --> 16:42.960
Just talking, you know,
they were saying that, er,

16:43.080 --> 16:46.560
you...you don't sleep or something.

16:46.680 --> 16:48.160
You can't sleep.

16:50.240 --> 16:53.400
When I do sleep, I dream.

16:54.680 --> 16:58.480
And in my dream,
someone wants my crown.

16:58.600 --> 17:00.960
I think it might be Michael.

17:02.080 --> 17:03.920
Call me at three.

17:10.920 --> 17:13.040
Arthur, I'm gonna put
that bullet on a necklace

17:13.160 --> 17:14.360
and wear it as a reminder.

17:15.320 --> 17:16.880
Arthur?

17:17.000 --> 17:19.360
- I heard you.
- You got trouble for me, then?

17:19.480 --> 17:20.960
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

17:33.560 --> 17:34.920
(GRUNTS)

17:36.000 --> 17:38.640
Mr Shelby,
the...the police are here to see you.

17:38.760 --> 17:40.160
Police aren't allowed in here.

17:40.280 --> 17:43.280
Er, he's not in uniform
and said it's very unofficial.

17:45.240 --> 17:46.360
(DOOR CLOSES)

17:48.800 --> 17:51.320
Afternoon. Someone get you some tea?

17:51.440 --> 17:52.760
No, I'm fine, Mr Shelby.

17:52.880 --> 17:54.160
- This won't take long.
- Good.

17:55.240 --> 17:57.120
You've got five minutes.

17:57.240 --> 18:01.680
Mr Shelby,
there was a shooting two days ago.

18:01.800 --> 18:03.520
A man died.

18:03.640 --> 18:05.040
It was a murder.

18:07.160 --> 18:08.200
In Maida Vale.

18:09.640 --> 18:10.720
Of all places.

18:13.520 --> 18:15.320
- His name was Levitt.
- Uh-huh.

18:18.000 --> 18:19.520
He was a journalist.

18:30.360 --> 18:33.360
The night before he was shot,
he came here to see you.

18:33.480 --> 18:37.840
We found a Commons pass
and your name in his diary.

18:37.960 --> 18:42.360
I was wondering
what his business here was.

18:43.680 --> 18:44.840
And I'm wondering...

18:46.000 --> 18:47.960
...what your business here is.

18:49.840 --> 18:52.600
According to his diary,
you knew him from Birmingham.

18:52.720 --> 18:53.960
What's your name?

18:55.240 --> 18:56.280
Stacker.

18:56.400 --> 18:58.200
Stacker. OK.

19:00.640 --> 19:03.800
Mr Shelby, Mr Levitt was a queer.

19:03.920 --> 19:05.920
Some may think
it was one of his queer friends...

19:06.040 --> 19:07.600
Mr Stacker,

19:07.720 --> 19:11.280
I get the feeling that,
with a little provocation,

19:11.400 --> 19:13.240
you could be very persistent.

19:13.360 --> 19:15.560
Only within my remit.

19:15.680 --> 19:17.960
Well, your Chief Constable Wyatt,

19:18.080 --> 19:21.560
he has clear views about persistence,
which he has shared with me.

19:21.680 --> 19:22.720
Mr Shelby...

19:22.840 --> 19:26.480
He likes persistence, as do I.
And thoroughness.

19:26.600 --> 19:27.840
But not frivolity.

19:29.440 --> 19:35.560
A man who walks in the park with other men
dies in Maida Vale.

19:35.680 --> 19:37.800
And you come to me?

19:37.920 --> 19:40.720
As well as his diary,
we have his notebook.

19:40.840 --> 19:43.240
(CLOCK CHIMES)

19:43.360 --> 19:46.040
Your time's up, Mr Stacker.

19:55.320 --> 19:56.560
Thank you.

19:59.640 --> 20:02.080
(DOOR CLOSES)

20:36.600 --> 20:37.720
Hello, Mum.

20:40.360 --> 20:41.920
This is Gina.

20:43.040 --> 20:44.520
Gina Gray.

20:46.240 --> 20:48.080
The captain married us on board.

20:51.080 --> 20:52.720
She's my wife, Mum. At least look at her.

20:52.840 --> 20:56.560
Tommy said to ask you
to tell me the truth.

20:57.640 --> 21:00.240
We've been travelling for 15 days,
Mrs Gray.

21:00.360 --> 21:01.760
Maybe we could talk about this
at another time.

21:01.880 --> 21:02.800
Yes.

21:02.920 --> 21:04.200
Let's go home and we can talk.

21:04.320 --> 21:08.680
You have no home
until you tell me the truth.

21:08.800 --> 21:10.240
Here?

21:10.360 --> 21:12.280
Yeah.

21:14.920 --> 21:16.280
ARTHUR: Michael!

21:19.080 --> 21:20.440
Hello, love.

21:22.000 --> 21:25.000
Welcome to Birmingham, eh?

21:26.360 --> 21:28.160
Michael?

21:29.640 --> 21:30.840
OK.

21:33.080 --> 21:35.200
Our ship docked at Belfast.

21:35.320 --> 21:36.920
I was then taken off the ship by two men.

21:37.040 --> 21:37.960
At gunpoint.

21:38.080 --> 21:40.120
I'm speaking to my son.

21:40.240 --> 21:41.400
Fuck you.

21:42.920 --> 21:44.600
Fuck you too, Arthur.

21:44.720 --> 21:49.280
This is my fucking wife.
I bring her home... To this?

21:52.080 --> 21:54.360
Come on, Gina.

21:57.600 --> 22:00.160
Well, where are you going now, eh? Hmm?

22:00.280 --> 22:02.000
Introduce me at least.

22:02.120 --> 22:04.320
- Excuse me.
- Look at this.

22:04.440 --> 22:06.360
Look at this.

22:06.480 --> 22:08.400
This is it, Gina.

22:08.520 --> 22:11.680
This is my fucking people.

22:11.800 --> 22:13.960
Do you want to know the truth, Arthur?

22:14.080 --> 22:15.440
Do you want to know the truth, Mum?

22:16.640 --> 22:22.040
I did not betray my fucking family!

22:23.320 --> 22:25.400
Now, Mum...

22:26.760 --> 22:27.880
...I want to go home.

22:29.680 --> 22:32.600
POLLY: I've booked you a suite
at the Midland Hotel.

22:34.080 --> 22:36.440
MICHAEL:
Was that Tommy's orders, then, was it?

22:36.560 --> 22:39.720
See, the Midland Hotel
is Tommy's little kingdom.

22:41.160 --> 22:44.120
Where all the porters keep an eye,

22:44.240 --> 22:47.720
where all the telephone exchange girls
are reporting on my calls.

22:47.840 --> 22:54.120
Yeah, well, why don't you think of it
like, er, quarantine, Michael, eh?

22:54.240 --> 22:57.720
We'll treat you like a fucking dog, hmm?

22:59.400 --> 23:00.880
Smelly one.

23:01.000 --> 23:02.280
Stinking one.

23:03.280 --> 23:08.000
Until we know you're clean, hmm?

23:08.120 --> 23:10.080
Fuck you, Arthur.

23:10.200 --> 23:12.000
Stand aside, Arthur.

23:12.120 --> 23:13.680
No, Poll.

23:21.480 --> 23:22.600
Come on, baby.

23:22.720 --> 23:24.440
Forget about 'em.

23:24.560 --> 23:27.640
Go and phone Tommy, tell him.

23:27.760 --> 23:30.480
Polly says Michael's telling the truth.

23:30.600 --> 23:33.120
GINA: It's all right. Forget about 'em.

23:33.240 --> 23:34.240
All right, Poll.

23:36.960 --> 23:38.880
Nice coat.

23:39.000 --> 23:40.800
What are you like? Camel, right?

23:43.640 --> 23:44.640
Oh.

23:46.400 --> 23:50.680
Welcome to the family, Gina Gray.

23:53.760 --> 23:57.560
THOMAS: I applaud the attempt by Mr Rowley
in the Education Bill

23:57.680 --> 24:00.480
to raise the school leaving age to 15.

24:00.600 --> 24:02.360
I also support...

24:18.000 --> 24:20.520
...as regards means-testing of any kind,

24:20.640 --> 24:22.240
- we are the people...
- MEMBERS: Yeah!

24:22.360 --> 24:25.320
- ...we've had enough.
- MEMBERS: Yeah!

24:25.440 --> 24:28.440
"We are the people,
and we've had enough."

24:28.560 --> 24:30.280
I move in favour of the amendment.

24:46.040 --> 24:47.240
Mr Shelby.

24:48.920 --> 24:52.320
I must say,
you sing like a songbird in the House.

24:54.000 --> 24:56.120
And who is this pretty finch?

24:56.240 --> 24:57.160
My sister.

24:57.280 --> 24:58.320
Who's pregnant.

24:58.440 --> 24:59.600
And dangerous.

24:59.720 --> 25:02.280
- (CLEARS HIS THROAT)
- Oh, we adore dangerous.

25:02.400 --> 25:03.800
Who's <i>we?</i>

25:03.920 --> 25:06.240
It's a collective noun,

25:06.360 --> 25:10.520
in this case describing a group of people
who are impatient and young and,

25:10.640 --> 25:13.080
as I have said, adore dangerous.

25:14.800 --> 25:18.120
Mr Shelby, you had a horse of that name.

25:20.280 --> 25:21.640
Whiskey. Irish.

25:21.760 --> 25:24.160
Give him one from my bottle.

25:24.280 --> 25:26.600
And one for myself.
In fact, bring the bottle.

25:27.760 --> 25:28.720
And the lady?

25:28.840 --> 25:30.360
Isn't thirsty.

25:30.480 --> 25:32.120
How do you know about the horse?

25:34.000 --> 25:36.040
We have a mutual acquaintance.

25:37.120 --> 25:38.240
May Car let on.

25:38.360 --> 25:42.160
When I asked about you, she said,
"Oh, my goodness, where do I begin?"

25:43.560 --> 25:45.960
And why were you asking after me?

25:46.080 --> 25:48.520
Because, as I have said,

25:48.640 --> 25:50.480
I adore dangerous.

25:51.560 --> 25:53.240
And where did she begin?

25:53.360 --> 25:56.280
You know, I was rather hoping
we might have this meeting alone.

25:56.400 --> 25:58.840
My sister is my political adviser.

25:58.960 --> 26:02.320
And my advice just now was,
"Don't meet Mr Mosley."

26:02.440 --> 26:04.240
Because I am dangerous?

26:04.360 --> 26:06.240
No.

26:06.360 --> 26:09.000
What is it you are impatient for,
Mr Mosley?

26:09.120 --> 26:12.840
I'm impatient for my fucking whiskey.

26:15.400 --> 26:16.640
Bennett!

26:18.920 --> 26:20.920
May Car let on spoke about you

26:21.040 --> 26:24.800
the way I imagine one might
about a party they barely remember,

26:24.920 --> 26:27.720
where you crash the car
into the dovecote

26:27.840 --> 26:31.200
and live on champagne and cocaine
for three whole days.

26:31.320 --> 26:32.840
You know, that kind of party.

26:32.960 --> 26:35.000
Only three days?

26:36.320 --> 26:37.440
Hmm.

26:41.400 --> 26:44.640
My sister advised against meeting you

26:44.760 --> 26:49.200
because it appears
you are moving away from the party...

26:50.720 --> 26:52.800
...in a different direction.

26:52.920 --> 26:55.120
And which direction is that?

26:55.240 --> 26:57.360
Towards fascism.

26:57.480 --> 27:01.640
"We are the people,
and we have had enough."

27:03.560 --> 27:05.280
I thought that was excellent.

27:06.560 --> 27:09.920
In which direction are you heading,
Mr Shelby?

27:10.040 --> 27:12.760
I am my own revolution.

27:12.880 --> 27:15.560
And you prefer Irish to Scotch.

27:17.480 --> 27:18.720
As do I.

27:18.840 --> 27:22.720
Like all things regarding Ireland,
it is...complex.

27:22.840 --> 27:23.880
Yes?

27:31.160 --> 27:32.800
Oh!

27:33.880 --> 27:36.800
Where do you stand
on the Irish question, Mr Shelby?

27:36.920 --> 27:39.640
Never been asked it.

27:39.760 --> 27:41.960
Then perhaps it's time you were.

27:42.080 --> 27:46.880
Tommy, I am the people,
and I have had enough.

27:47.000 --> 27:49.560
We are looking for someone
to begin a dialogue...

27:49.680 --> 27:51.960
...with certain elements in Belfast

27:52.080 --> 27:54.920
with whom
we don't officially have any dealings.

27:55.040 --> 27:58.480
I'll be too busy singing in the House.

27:58.600 --> 28:00.720
It would involve a promotion.

28:02.360 --> 28:05.760
Junior Minister to the Duchy of Lancaster.

28:06.840 --> 28:08.560
Birmingham is my concern.

28:08.680 --> 28:13.640
Ireland bores me.
Thanks for the whiskey, Mr Mosley.

28:15.160 --> 28:16.720
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)

28:20.600 --> 28:22.400
Hmm.

28:22.520 --> 28:24.640
What the fuck was that about?

28:24.760 --> 28:27.800
Ireland. It's been Ireland's day
all fucking day long.

28:27.920 --> 28:28.840
What do you mean?

28:28.960 --> 28:32.560
Ada, go home and start calling
anyone who had dealings

28:32.680 --> 28:35.160
with Shelby Company Limited
while you were in Boston.

28:35.280 --> 28:36.440
Ask them about Michael.

28:38.200 --> 28:40.200
Ask them what about him?

28:40.320 --> 28:42.600
Who he's been seeing,
who he's been meeting,

28:42.720 --> 28:45.400
- what deals he's made.
- Why?

28:45.520 --> 28:50.080
Ask 'em especially about people
he's met from Glasgow or Belfast.

28:50.200 --> 28:53.560
Tommy,
why don't you come back with me, eh?

28:53.680 --> 28:55.560
You can play chess with Karl.

28:55.680 --> 28:57.520
I'll make some calls,
you can listen in.

28:57.640 --> 28:58.600
Drive home tomorrow.

28:58.720 --> 29:01.320
That bastard starts talking
about Irish whiskey.

29:01.440 --> 29:02.680
The fuck does he know? Eh?

29:02.800 --> 29:05.640
More than me, Tommy.
What are you talking about?

29:05.760 --> 29:08.920
I'm talking about an empty chair, Ada.

29:09.040 --> 29:11.240
My chair. My throne.

29:11.360 --> 29:12.920
People thinking I'm gonna fall,

29:13.040 --> 29:15.440
they start behaving
in a different way around you.

29:15.560 --> 29:16.920
Who thinks that?

29:17.040 --> 29:19.200
They start to circle.

29:19.320 --> 29:21.320
Who's going to take the throne, eh?

29:21.440 --> 29:23.760
Linda, she wants some for Arthur,

29:23.880 --> 29:26.320
Aberama Gold, people in the north,
Michael...

29:26.440 --> 29:28.600
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)

29:31.040 --> 29:34.200
Just go home, make some calls.

29:34.320 --> 29:36.200
Protestants are coming, I think.

29:36.320 --> 29:38.320
I need to get back to Birmingham.

29:40.000 --> 29:41.560
(SIGHS)

29:51.240 --> 29:52.840
Polly.

29:52.960 --> 29:54.440
Are you armed?

29:55.800 --> 29:57.720
Yeah.

29:57.840 --> 29:59.040
Yeah.

29:59.160 --> 30:01.480
Would you please consider
putting your weapons behind the bar

30:01.600 --> 30:04.000
in case feelings begin to run high?

30:04.120 --> 30:05.680
Behind the bar, Poll, eh?

30:06.920 --> 30:08.720
Behind my own bar, yeah?

30:15.600 --> 30:16.640
I prefer it there.

30:19.320 --> 30:21.040
Thomas?

30:29.280 --> 30:31.040
I had a dream...

30:31.160 --> 30:34.600
...about a black cat last night, Poll.

30:36.480 --> 30:39.920
A black cat dream
means there is a traitor close by.

30:40.040 --> 30:41.680
It was you who taught me that.

30:41.800 --> 30:44.200
Black cat can mean lots of things.

30:44.320 --> 30:46.760
Can mean you're hurting yourself.

30:46.880 --> 30:48.000
Betraying yourself.

30:49.480 --> 30:51.680
Are you seeing things, Thomas?

30:54.080 --> 30:55.200
Yes, I am.

30:55.320 --> 30:56.920
(CAR APPROACHES)

30:57.040 --> 30:59.440
Yes, I am. Very clearly.

31:01.160 --> 31:02.960
Coming from every fucking direction.

31:04.960 --> 31:06.760
(CAR ENGINE STOPS)

31:07.840 --> 31:09.320
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

31:11.640 --> 31:13.200
(BAR DOOR CREAKS OPEN)

31:17.240 --> 31:18.320
Tommy.

31:19.800 --> 31:21.680
I'd like to introduce you to my wife.

31:23.760 --> 31:26.240
I would also like to, er, say something.

31:26.360 --> 31:28.880
- Sit down, Michael.
- I betrayed you.

31:29.000 --> 31:31.640
- Michael.
- But only in my heart.

31:31.760 --> 31:33.440
There was a time,

31:33.560 --> 31:35.000
in America,

31:35.120 --> 31:37.440
and there was a lot of money in that bank.

31:37.560 --> 31:39.680
And I wondered
if I could...I could leave,

31:39.800 --> 31:41.720
move to California.

31:41.840 --> 31:43.840
Someone said I should invest in pictures.

31:45.120 --> 31:46.240
Hollywood.

31:47.480 --> 31:48.920
But Gina stopped me.

31:50.240 --> 31:53.200
- Gina said...
- I told you to sit down, Michael.

32:01.960 --> 32:03.000
Now, tell me...

32:04.760 --> 32:06.880
...what happened on that ship

32:07.000 --> 32:08.720
in Belfast harbour.

32:11.680 --> 32:14.920
On the journey back from New York,
we got married.

32:15.040 --> 32:16.800
But we needed to find a witness.

32:16.920 --> 32:18.120
A purser.

32:18.240 --> 32:19.640
He was from Belfast.

32:19.760 --> 32:20.840
We got friendly.

32:20.960 --> 32:22.160
What happened when the ship docked?

32:24.600 --> 32:29.120
This purser had friends who ran
a whiskey distillery in County Tyrone.

32:29.240 --> 32:31.600
They wanted a way
of getting their stuff into America.

32:31.720 --> 32:34.360
So I said, "OK, invite them aboard."

32:34.480 --> 32:37.760
When they came in, I realised
that they didn't make whiskey.

32:37.880 --> 32:39.720
They were Scottish. From Glasgow.

32:39.840 --> 32:42.400
Couldn't understood
a fucking word they were saying.

32:42.520 --> 32:45.040
They started swearing,

32:45.160 --> 32:46.760
so I asked Gina to leave.

32:47.840 --> 32:50.760
That was when they started talking
about you, Tom.

32:50.880 --> 32:54.360
They said that Tommy Shelby
was a spent force,

32:54.480 --> 32:56.680
that politics had got to him...

32:58.200 --> 33:00.000
...that he was spent in the head,

33:00.120 --> 33:02.680
that now was a good time to move in

33:02.800 --> 33:04.800
and did I want to be part of it.

33:04.920 --> 33:07.480
They knew about the money we lost
in America.

33:07.600 --> 33:09.120
They said that you were going to blame me.

33:09.240 --> 33:11.600
That you had a bullet with my name on it.

33:14.080 --> 33:15.560
What did you say, Michael?

33:15.680 --> 33:17.000
I didn't have time to say anything.

33:18.240 --> 33:20.040
Coppers came on board.

33:20.160 --> 33:21.440
Well, I thought they were coppers.

33:21.560 --> 33:22.720
They, er...

33:24.200 --> 33:25.760
They were IRA.

33:25.880 --> 33:27.040
Exactly.

33:32.880 --> 33:35.800
And the first men from Glasgow?

33:37.600 --> 33:42.640
The IRA commander said the men
from Glasgow were called Billy Boys.

33:43.640 --> 33:45.040
Fucking Billy Boys.

33:45.160 --> 33:47.200
I don't know who the fuck Billy Boys are.

33:47.320 --> 33:53.040
They run every man in every coalmine,
on every shipyard east of Glasgow.

33:53.160 --> 33:57.120
Ties with Belfast, UVF.

33:57.240 --> 33:59.080
Protestant razor gang.

33:59.200 --> 34:02.040
They also dabble in politics.

34:02.160 --> 34:06.480
You know, muscle for fascist rallies.

34:06.600 --> 34:09.280
But you did no deal, Michael?

34:09.400 --> 34:11.400
You didn't even know who they were?

34:11.520 --> 34:14.240
I was too busy looking forward
to giving you the good news.

34:15.920 --> 34:19.680
The reason Gina and I got married
on the ship was because Gina is pregnant.

34:21.160 --> 34:23.040
You're going to be a grandmother.

34:31.480 --> 34:32.760
OK, Michael.

34:34.360 --> 34:35.720
I believe you.

34:35.840 --> 34:37.160
Welcome home.

34:38.440 --> 34:39.520
Congratulations.

34:40.680 --> 34:42.640
Just remember...

34:42.760 --> 34:47.240
Your unborn child has witnessed
what you said.

34:47.360 --> 34:49.800
- Thomas!
- And it will be born according to...

34:49.920 --> 34:50.920
You fuck!

34:51.040 --> 34:54.400
Where the fuck are you going, hmm?

34:54.520 --> 34:56.440
Are you fucking mad, hmm?

34:58.920 --> 35:03.920
- You are free to fucking leave, Michael.
- You fucking bastard.

35:04.040 --> 35:06.240
But you're not free, Michael, are you?

35:07.960 --> 35:10.080
You lost this company a lot of money.

35:10.200 --> 35:11.520
I told you to sell...

35:13.360 --> 35:14.680
...but you held on,

35:14.800 --> 35:19.520
and now I want you to pay me back
what you owe me.

35:19.640 --> 35:23.800
There is work you can do,
there are risks you can take.

35:23.920 --> 35:25.840
We were close before.

35:25.960 --> 35:27.800
Now I want you closer still.

35:30.120 --> 35:32.160
Michael, honey.

35:33.840 --> 35:35.200
Look at your cousin.

35:36.440 --> 35:37.800
He's in trouble, huh?

35:39.240 --> 35:40.560
He needs you.

35:43.360 --> 35:45.280
Come on, baby, let's go.

36:10.040 --> 36:11.600
Fucking cheek of her, eh?

36:13.560 --> 36:15.640
Mad Dog Jimmy.

36:15.760 --> 36:17.840
Coming south.

36:22.600 --> 36:24.120
Not so mad any more.

36:24.240 --> 36:26.280
He's got friends in high places
these days.

36:29.440 --> 36:31.600
Black cat dream is never wrong, brother.

36:42.880 --> 36:45.040
(HORSE NEIGHS)

37:19.600 --> 37:21.000
(GUNSHOT)

37:21.120 --> 37:23.760
(GROANS)

37:23.880 --> 37:28.520
# Hello, hello, we are the Billy Boys

37:28.640 --> 37:32.360
# Hello, hello, we are the Billy Boys

37:32.480 --> 37:36.920
# We're up to our knees in Fenian blood
Surrender or you'll die

37:37.040 --> 37:40.840
# We are the Brigton Derry Billy Boys. #

37:43.880 --> 37:46.200
Drop the peashooter, son.

37:50.800 --> 37:55.120
A broken broom stops
all Gypsy curses, Mr Gold.

37:55.240 --> 37:58.600
Ah! (GROANS)

37:58.720 --> 37:59.960
(COUGHS)

38:00.080 --> 38:01.800
Who the fuck are you?

38:01.920 --> 38:03.800
Did you not hear my song?

38:03.920 --> 38:07.440
These gentlemen are the Billy Boys.

38:10.680 --> 38:12.400
And me?

38:16.080 --> 38:17.200
I'm Jimmy.

38:17.320 --> 38:20.000
Ah, fuck, fuck.

38:20.120 --> 38:21.320
Good.

38:21.440 --> 38:23.920
Mouth broke, so you can't talk.

38:24.040 --> 38:26.520
But you don't need to.

38:26.640 --> 38:29.360
Your body will be the lesson.

38:30.560 --> 38:35.680
You work in a particular capacity
for Mr Thomas Shelby, OBE.

38:35.800 --> 38:37.120
Am I right?

38:43.920 --> 38:45.040
I heard you're a fighter.

38:47.040 --> 38:48.040
The best.

38:49.800 --> 38:52.400
But your fighting days are over.

38:52.520 --> 38:54.880
(GROANS)

38:55.000 --> 38:58.600
Because I need Mr Shelby to understand...

38:58.720 --> 39:02.000
...that his best...

39:02.120 --> 39:06.440
...is not...good enough.

39:06.560 --> 39:10.040
(MUFFLED SCREAMS)

39:13.920 --> 39:15.560
(MUFFLED SCREAMS)

39:41.720 --> 39:43.280
(MUFFLED SCREAMS)

39:48.120 --> 39:49.640
(GROANS)

39:57.280 --> 39:58.280
Bonnie!

39:59.560 --> 40:01.880
Farewell, fighter boy. You died well.

40:03.240 --> 40:04.440
(HORSE NEIGHS)

40:06.240 --> 40:07.440
(LABOURED BREATHING)

40:09.000 --> 40:10.960
(WHEEZES)

40:12.320 --> 40:14.400
(SOBS) Bonnie...

40:14.520 --> 40:16.120
Bonnie!

40:29.920 --> 40:33.400
Tell Tommy Shelby
it's time to fucking share.

40:35.640 --> 40:38.560
We'll take all the tracks out
as far as Nottingham.

40:38.680 --> 40:40.520
We'll take Cheltenham as well.

40:42.000 --> 40:46.080
Otherwise, it will be Thomas Shelby
who's crucified,

40:46.200 --> 40:48.800
and there will be no resurrection.

40:48.920 --> 40:50.880
(GROANS)

40:51.000 --> 40:52.320
(COUGHS)

40:52.440 --> 40:54.120
Come on, boys.

41:09.600 --> 41:11.920
(WHEEZES)

41:12.040 --> 41:14.560
(SOBS)

41:14.880 --> 41:16.080
(SINGING INSIDE PUB)

41:19.000 --> 41:20.960
# But when you're crying

41:21.080 --> 41:27.440
# You bring out the rain
So stop your crying... #

41:27.560 --> 41:28.680
(MUSIC STOPS)

41:38.800 --> 41:41.720
Ladies and gentlemen, I'm just going to
take a short break. Thank you.

41:43.120 --> 41:44.960
Yeah. Good man.

41:51.720 --> 41:56.560
Beautiful, Billy, beautiful.
Really nice. Really nice.

42:00.920 --> 42:04.240
Really meaningful, you know?
A heartfelt song.

42:04.360 --> 42:07.080
I like it. I really do.

42:07.200 --> 42:11.280
Boys, this here is Billy Grade.

42:12.520 --> 42:14.000
Man I was telling you about, son.

42:16.120 --> 42:18.440
- Billy, this here's my kid brother, Finn.
- Hey.

42:19.880 --> 42:22.760
Have a drink, Billy.

42:22.880 --> 42:24.160
I can't, my voice is...

42:24.280 --> 42:26.600
Drink, Bill.

42:26.720 --> 42:27.960
Yeah.

42:29.080 --> 42:30.240
Yeah.

42:35.400 --> 42:37.240
You boys won't remember...

42:38.360 --> 42:42.240
...but I remember when Billy here
made a living on the football pitch.

42:42.360 --> 42:43.280
(LAUGHS)

42:43.400 --> 42:45.880
Oh, yeah, that was a long time ago,
Mr Shelby.

42:46.000 --> 42:47.520
- Yeah, what a left foot, eh?
- Yeah.

42:47.640 --> 42:48.960
(BOTH LAUGH)

42:49.080 --> 42:53.960
And then what? Manager, right? Hmm?

42:54.080 --> 42:56.640
Well, yeah, and now I'm a singer.

42:56.760 --> 42:57.920
Are you?

42:59.000 --> 43:03.920
Every football team in England
knows Billy Grade.

43:04.040 --> 43:07.800
And he knows a few people, too.
Don't you, Bill, eh? Hmm?

43:07.920 --> 43:10.160
- One or two.
- Useful.

43:11.320 --> 43:13.680
Very useful.

43:13.800 --> 43:15.800
But what do you do, Bill, eh?

43:15.920 --> 43:17.680
Hmm?

43:17.800 --> 43:22.280
You're in here, singing -
or whatever the fuck you call it -

43:22.400 --> 43:25.640
in shit-hole pubs in Birmingham.

43:25.760 --> 43:28.480
(TUTS)

43:28.600 --> 43:30.880
It's no way to make a living, boys.

43:31.960 --> 43:34.160
- Degrading.
- I love it.

43:34.280 --> 43:36.440
I really do, I love it.

43:37.600 --> 43:40.800
And thank you, by the way,
for inviting me here tonight.

43:40.920 --> 43:42.480
I really appreciate it,
so thank you very much.

43:42.600 --> 43:44.040
Don't thank me.

43:44.160 --> 43:46.080
I didn't invite you here to sing.

43:48.200 --> 43:52.600
If I wanted to listen to music,
I'd buy an Al Jolson record. Hmm?

43:52.720 --> 43:54.880
That's what I'd do.

43:55.000 --> 43:57.320
Real singer, you know?

43:57.440 --> 43:58.920
Melody.

43:59.040 --> 44:00.840
Tune.

44:02.920 --> 44:05.640
So what is it that you want...exactly?

44:09.320 --> 44:13.160
Finn will explain
the nature of my proposition.

44:14.720 --> 44:16.800
You'll listen to him, won't you, Bill, eh?

44:16.920 --> 44:19.640
- You'll be attentive, won't you?
- Yeah, of course, course.

44:19.760 --> 44:20.680
Because Isiah here,

44:20.800 --> 44:24.120
he'll show you the fucking consequences
if you don't.

44:26.600 --> 44:27.840
All right?

44:30.920 --> 44:33.200
I'll leave you with the bottle, hmm?

44:47.280 --> 44:49.280
What proposition?

44:49.400 --> 44:52.320
Right, what I want from you, Billy,

44:52.440 --> 44:57.160
is for you to write down
a name and a number

44:57.280 --> 44:59.920
next to every one of those football teams,
yeah?

45:00.040 --> 45:01.720
- Why?
- Why?

45:01.840 --> 45:03.800
People like to bet on those kind of things
these days.

45:03.920 --> 45:06.040
- We are a gambling enterprise.
- I know who you are.

45:06.160 --> 45:09.920
To fix a horse race,
you give the outsider a bit of cocaine.

45:10.040 --> 45:11.800
- Jesus!
- To fix a football match,

45:11.920 --> 45:14.280
you give the goalkeeper £20.

45:25.680 --> 45:28.560
You're a Peaky Blinder now, Billy.

45:28.680 --> 45:29.840
Hmm?

45:38.000 --> 45:40.000
What have you got there?

45:41.560 --> 45:42.880
I've written a letter.

45:43.000 --> 45:44.400
Oh.

45:47.520 --> 45:48.880
Who for?

45:49.000 --> 45:50.760
For you.

45:50.880 --> 45:52.920
And Lizzie's written one to Tommy.

45:55.760 --> 45:57.000
Well...

45:58.120 --> 45:59.440
...can I read it?

45:59.560 --> 46:00.960
It's not finished yet.

46:02.280 --> 46:04.440
I'm getting rid of the parts
I wrote when I was drunk.

46:06.160 --> 46:08.080
By the way, I've stopped drinking.

46:08.200 --> 46:11.040
And your bottles of snow
I poured down the lavatory.

46:12.560 --> 46:14.320
When I was drunk, I was too hard on you.

46:14.440 --> 46:15.960
It's...it's not your fault.

46:21.160 --> 46:22.520
So...

46:24.680 --> 46:26.440
That letter's about me, is it?

46:26.560 --> 46:27.640
Yeah.

46:28.920 --> 46:30.720
- Hmm.
- And about me.

46:31.960 --> 46:33.880
About the future. About the company.

46:35.920 --> 46:37.000
Lizzie and I...

46:37.120 --> 46:40.240
Sat here and made things worse
the last few hours, hmm?

46:40.360 --> 46:42.360
Yeah, and we've come up with a plan.

46:42.480 --> 46:44.520
Oh, you've come up with a plan, eh?

46:44.640 --> 46:47.240
Lizzie says Tommy won't live
two more years if he carries on like this.

46:47.360 --> 46:48.280
He's gone too far.

46:48.400 --> 46:49.960
Is that what Lizzie says, hmm?

46:50.080 --> 46:51.240
Really now?

46:51.360 --> 46:54.000
Well, how far has he gone, hmm, Linda?
How far?

46:54.120 --> 46:56.320
He's lost all the legitimate money
in America.

46:56.440 --> 46:58.680
No. No, that was Michael.

46:58.800 --> 47:01.680
He's fixing races. He's fixing football.

47:01.800 --> 47:04.720
Following the financial crisis,
the Shelby Company Limited

47:04.840 --> 47:08.040
has to find other sources of cash income.

47:08.160 --> 47:09.840
Tommy went into Chinatown.

47:09.960 --> 47:13.440
He's selling out the Communists
to the British intelligence.

47:13.560 --> 47:16.320
And all the time, every day,
he gets more and more famous.

47:16.440 --> 47:17.640
But that's OK.

47:17.760 --> 47:19.920
Because if anyone puts
two and two together...

47:20.040 --> 47:21.240
That wasn't us.

47:21.360 --> 47:22.920
- (CHUCKLES)
- It's not fucking us!

47:23.040 --> 47:25.800
It's going to blow up, Arthur!
It can't sustain.

47:25.920 --> 47:28.280
- You know it.
- Oh, yeah? And what do you know, eh?

47:28.400 --> 47:29.960
You've worked it all out.

47:30.080 --> 47:32.120
You and fucking Lizzie, eh?

47:32.240 --> 47:35.840
Got it all planned out, is that right?

47:35.960 --> 47:38.040
And I tell you,

47:38.160 --> 47:42.120
all you're gonna do
is you're gonna be the good fucking wife.

47:42.240 --> 47:44.920
Yeah, like the perfect couple.

47:45.040 --> 47:47.040
We'll go upstairs, hmm?

47:47.160 --> 47:49.760
We'll go upstairs.

47:49.880 --> 47:52.400
Yeah, make love, hmm?

48:03.040 --> 48:06.520
I spent my day writing two letters
and deciding which one to give.

48:08.600 --> 48:10.440
Looks like I'll have to give
the other one.

48:13.200 --> 48:14.480
What other one?

48:15.480 --> 48:17.440
What fucking other one?!

48:20.520 --> 48:22.000
What did you do with my letter?

48:34.280 --> 48:35.440
I burnt it.

48:37.520 --> 48:38.680
So did Arthur.

48:40.840 --> 48:43.360
- Did you read it first?
- Yes.

48:44.560 --> 48:45.840
That's more than Arthur did.

48:47.960 --> 48:49.320
(GROANS)

48:51.680 --> 48:53.720
Didn't help that you can't fucking spell.

48:55.360 --> 48:56.960
I left school too early.

48:58.160 --> 49:00.200
Did you read the bit about the lawyers?

49:00.320 --> 49:01.480
Do you want to fuck?

49:02.920 --> 49:04.040
Didn't think so.

49:06.680 --> 49:08.320
- You don't want to eat?
- No.

49:09.520 --> 49:10.840
- You've got calls?
- Yeah.

49:19.720 --> 49:21.680
It's Ruby's birthday today, Tommy.

49:25.120 --> 49:27.960
Do you know why I took her to Arthur's?

49:28.080 --> 49:29.840
Because she said she's scared of you.

49:31.640 --> 49:34.360
When she knows you're not coming home,
she's a different kid.

49:36.480 --> 49:38.000
But I've bought a cake.

49:38.120 --> 49:39.360
And I want you there.

49:40.520 --> 49:41.760
We're in the drawing room.

49:42.920 --> 49:44.040
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDE)

49:46.320 --> 49:47.320
Lizzie...

49:49.600 --> 49:50.600
(FOOTSTEPS STOP)

49:52.840 --> 49:54.160
I'm in a room...

49:55.560 --> 49:57.600
...and they're coming at me.

49:59.760 --> 50:01.480
It's OK. I want 'em to.

50:03.360 --> 50:05.040
Last thing I want is silence.

50:07.280 --> 50:08.920
Standing up there, in silence,

50:09.040 --> 50:10.360
and someone says...

50:13.240 --> 50:15.680
..."Sorry about all that noise.

50:15.800 --> 50:19.240
"Sorry about all that...dust.

50:20.280 --> 50:22.360
"Sorry about all that mud.

50:22.480 --> 50:24.520
"And all that fucking blood."

50:26.080 --> 50:28.400
And you say, "Don't be sorry.

50:28.520 --> 50:30.520
"Don't be sorry. It's all I can do now."

50:35.000 --> 50:37.120
You want me to write this down?

50:39.880 --> 50:41.840
Do you want me
to write you a fucking letter?

50:44.720 --> 50:46.520
Me and Arthur can't write it down...

50:48.000 --> 50:50.320
...cos they haven't invented
the fucking words.

50:54.120 --> 50:56.400
We don't have the fucking words.

50:59.840 --> 51:01.120
And the worst thing is...

51:03.240 --> 51:04.760
...could've stayed at school.

51:06.080 --> 51:08.160
But we volunteered.

51:10.200 --> 51:12.320
Still don't have the fucking words.

51:21.640 --> 51:23.520
Should you choose to depart, Tommy,

51:23.640 --> 51:25.920
either by your own hand
or someone else's,

51:26.040 --> 51:28.600
the person who would take your place
is me.

51:29.880 --> 51:31.040
Legally.

51:31.160 --> 51:32.800
Financially.

51:32.920 --> 51:34.000
Everything.

51:35.240 --> 51:37.040
I need to know there'll be something left.

51:38.240 --> 51:41.400
Well, you know, Lizzie, in my head,
I still pay you for it, so...

51:42.680 --> 51:44.280
...good luck with me.

51:45.560 --> 51:47.400
(PHONE RINGS)

51:51.920 --> 51:53.520
I have business.

52:04.240 --> 52:05.240
(DOOR CLOSES)

52:18.560 --> 52:21.880
# Happy birthday to you

52:22.000 --> 52:26.000
# Happy birthday to you... #

52:26.120 --> 52:28.080
Yeah, I wanna ask you some questions...

52:29.280 --> 52:31.440
...about the night you met Michael Gray.

52:38.840 --> 52:40.360
Make a wish.

52:40.480 --> 52:42.080
Yeah!

52:43.560 --> 52:47.080
(DISTORTED HEAVY BREATHING)

52:54.600 --> 52:57.160
(CAR ENGINE REVS)

53:04.800 --> 53:07.160
(REVVING CONTINUES)

53:07.280 --> 53:09.280
OK, kids, come on, let's go to bed.
Quickly.

53:09.400 --> 53:10.800
- Why?
- Who's coming?

53:10.920 --> 53:14.120
That's the thing, Charles, we don't know.
We never know.

53:33.040 --> 53:35.280
(GROANS)

53:35.400 --> 53:36.560
JOHNNY: Tommy!

53:39.320 --> 53:41.360
- Get out of the fucking car.
- Don't!

53:41.480 --> 53:45.080
Get out of the fucking car now,
or I'll open fire!

53:53.840 --> 53:55.880
ABERAMA: If you're looking for traitors,

53:56.000 --> 54:00.200
there's one...with his ribs mashed up.

54:00.320 --> 54:03.440
The man's gone fucking mad, Tom!

54:03.560 --> 54:05.600
You did this?

54:05.720 --> 54:07.680
With one arm and a hammer.

54:08.760 --> 54:12.560
And a mighty pain...and a mighty fury!

54:15.520 --> 54:16.920
They killed him.

54:19.120 --> 54:20.240
My son!

54:21.240 --> 54:24.760
They shot him and they put him
up on a fucking cross,

54:24.880 --> 54:26.560
and he's fucking dead!

54:27.600 --> 54:28.920
Who did?

54:42.000 --> 54:45.240
Only Johnny Dogs and his kin knew
where we were camped.

54:45.360 --> 54:47.920
No, Tom. No.
I swear to God, I never told a soul.

54:48.040 --> 54:50.560
- Get the fuck away!
- I never told a fucking soul.

54:50.680 --> 54:53.440
How could you fucking do this?!
My fucking son!

54:53.560 --> 54:56.440
(YELLING)

54:56.560 --> 54:58.080
They fucking took him from me!

54:58.200 --> 55:01.600
- My only...son!
- (COUGHS)

55:01.720 --> 55:02.880
Johnny!

55:03.000 --> 55:04.560
Tommy!

55:04.680 --> 55:06.440
Your shoulder is shattered.

55:06.560 --> 55:08.880
If you don't get it fixed,
you'll lose your arm.

55:09.000 --> 55:11.440
He's gone! Fucking killed him!

55:11.560 --> 55:14.480
Fucking son! My own fucking kin!

55:14.600 --> 55:15.960
THOMAS: Listen to me!

55:16.080 --> 55:20.400
How can a one-armed man
avenge the death of his son, eh?

55:26.160 --> 55:28.320
They crucified my son...

55:30.560 --> 55:31.720
...for you.

55:38.360 --> 55:40.080
(GUNSHOTS)

55:40.200 --> 55:44.440
Get away from my house! All of you!

55:44.560 --> 55:48.240
Get away from my child!

55:48.360 --> 55:50.680
This is my house.

55:50.800 --> 55:52.960
And I don't want you back.

55:53.080 --> 55:55.160
I don't want you back!

56:13.600 --> 56:15.320
If you want to take on the Billy Boys,

56:15.440 --> 56:16.520
you need me alive.

56:18.800 --> 56:21.000
Everyone fucking needs me.

56:23.960 --> 56:25.880
Call an ambulance,

56:26.000 --> 56:28.680
or a man will lose his arm.

56:42.040 --> 56:43.680
(SOBS)

56:48.560 --> 56:50.120
Come on, Johnny.

56:50.240 --> 56:52.480
Come on.

56:55.080 --> 56:56.160
Tom...

56:58.520 --> 57:00.560
I'm no black cat, Tom.

57:00.680 --> 57:02.520
I know, Johnny. I know.

57:04.160 --> 57:06.920
In all the world, of all of the people,

57:07.040 --> 57:08.960
you alone I know I can trust.

57:08.984 --> 57:13.984
http://hiqve.com/
